summary:
I wish we could've had spent more time with Tary. 
I mean we got a kind of whirlwind of information because VM was suspicious as...
body:
I wish we could’ve had spent more time with Tary.

I mean we got a kind of whirlwind of information because VM was suspicious as fuck after Scanlan, and also, you know, because they were assholes about it… And Tary was already a bit of an oversharer. But because everything was condensed in so few episodes I feel like there still was a lot of unexplored, deeper character history and personality insight that we skipped. Childhood. Adolescence. Fears. Triomphs. Mistakes. Growth.

I just miss that goof, and I wish I knew him better.

summary: So I'm watching CR with my partner who's only on episode 14 or so...
body:
So I’m watching CR with my partner who’s only on episode 14 or so…

So they’ve been good about spoilers and still doesnt know about episode 26. They’ve gotten to The Evening Nip though and have learned about Lucien, and want to know more about Molly’s story and I’m like same, but I cant say anything because I cant spoil it.

I really hope they can enjoy Caduceus as much as I do, but it still doesnt fix this story hole. I hope the Mighty Nein revisit it at least for some closure.

summary: I wonder how often Caleb experiences the “there’s a cat sleeping on me, therefore I can’t move ever again” phenomenon Like....he...
body:
I wonder how often Caleb experiences the “there’s a cat sleeping on me, therefore I can’t move ever again” phenomenon

Like….he controls Frumpkin, he can tell him to wake up and move, or click him back to his demi-plane, but I like to think Caleb would just be like “ja, well, I guess this is my life forever now” and go back to reading his book for five more hours

(Also, related: I wonder how often Caleb experiences the “there’s a goblin sleeping on me, therefore I can’t move ever again” phenomenon)
